
<p>Let \(x^{3}+a x^{2}+b x+8=0\) be a cubic equation with integer coefficients.
Suppose both \(r\) and \(-r\) are roots of this equation, where \(r>0\) is a real number.
List all possible pairs of values \((a, b)\).
</p>

Sol.

<p>
So the possible pairs of values of \(a, b\) are \(\{ (-8,-1), (-4,-2), (-2,-4), (-1,-8) \} \).
</p>


